# Single source of truth for the SPARQL Anything build used by the pipeline.
# Sourced by map.sh (host + container runtime) and by the Dockerfile (build-time download).
#
# Pinned to v1.2.0-RC1 for the fx:slice.size and fx:csv.quote-char fixes that config/places.rq
# relies on (SPARQL-Anything/sparql.anything#624 and #625). We previously pinned a nightly
# (snapshot-<date>-<time>) because it was the first build carrying those fixes, but nightly
# releases are pruned upstream after a few days: the tag disappeared and the pipeline downloaded
# a 404 page as bin/*.jar (“Invalid or corrupt jarfile”). RC and stable tags are permanent, so
# never pin a nightly here. Output was verified byte-identical to the last working nightly.
#
# The version tag and the jar filename differ, so both are set explicitly.
#
# The := defaults let an external environment variable override the pin (e.g. to test
# another build) without editing this file.
: "${SPARQL_ANYTHING_VERSION:=v1.2.0-RC1}"
: "${SPARQL_ANYTHING_JAR:=sparql-anything-1.2.0-RC1.jar}"
